<H2>Adding the New Image</H2>

<p>&nbsp; 
With the new image wright_flight.jpg downloaded.  You can now create anchors
on it and connect those anchors to Links.  To do this follow the following
actions.
</p>

<H3>Displaying the new image</H3>

<p> Display the image by using the Load Image command in the File menu
of Jimage. 
</p>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="images/wright_flight.jpg" WIDTH="639"
HEIGHT="451"></CENTER>

<H3>Creating Anchors on the new Image</H3>

<p> Create a couple of anchors on the image.  Make an anchor around the 
aircraft and another around Orville.
</p>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="images/wright_with_anchors.gif" WIDTH="642"
HEIGHT="452"></CENTER>

<H3>Connecting the Anchors to the Active Link</H3>

<p> Make sure that your are in bill_web and have selected places_to_go
as the active link.
</p>

<p> Put the mouse inside the anchor areas and click the right most 
mouse button.  A pop-up menu will display some choices for you to select
from.  Choose the add to Active Link command for each anchor.
</p>

<p> You have now made a Link which is connected to four anchors in three images.
(places_to_go should now be connecting anchors in wright_flight.jpg,
bill.gif, and earthrise.gif.)
Now you can traverse the link from the various anchors.
</p>

</BODY>
